1:17:53.794 --> 1:17:55.545
This is pretty important. Yeah.

1:17:55.629 --> 1:17:56.922
-Here it comes.
-Okay.

1:17:57.589 --> 1:18:01.635
Um, you all know that I love Christmas.

1:18:01.718 --> 1:18:02.594
Understatement.

1:18:02.678 --> 1:18:08.684
But this year I learned
that Christmas can come with challenges

1:18:08.767 --> 1:18:10.060
as well as gifts,

1:18:10.143 --> 1:18:13.605
and that it's the time of year to reflect.

1:18:13.689 --> 1:18:16.650
But reflection can sometimes be painful.

1:18:16.733 --> 1:18:21.738
But I know that I can embrace
whatever the season may bring.

1:18:22.948 --> 1:18:26.034
And that it's spending time
with the people you love

1:18:26.118 --> 1:18:27.911
that makes Christmas magical.

1:18:27.994 --> 1:18:31.540
Not just decorations or holiday events.

1:18:31.623 --> 1:18:32.833
Amen, brother.

1:18:32.916 --> 1:18:33.750
Right.

1:18:36.586 --> 1:18:38.588
Well, I want to say something too.

1:18:38.672 --> 1:18:40.048
Oh, here it comes.

1:18:40.132 --> 1:18:41.174
Yeah.

1:18:42.259 --> 1:18:46.388
Um, well, you all know
I was a little reluctant about Christmas.

1:18:46.471 --> 1:18:47.305
A little?

1:18:48.724 --> 1:18:50.726
But, Tom, you have taught me

1:18:50.809 --> 1:18:55.313
that it's not just
about strict traditions.

1:18:55.397 --> 1:18:56.898
It can be fun again.

1:18:57.482 --> 1:19:02.404
And there isn't always a Barbie
hiding in the closet to ruin everything.

1:19:04.364 --> 1:19:06.825
-A what now?
-Don't stop her. She's on a roll.

1:19:06.908 --> 1:19:08.034
Oh, okay.

1:19:08.577 --> 1:19:09.453
Tom.

1:19:10.078 --> 1:19:11.788
You did this thing for Ella.

1:19:13.039 --> 1:19:14.916
Not because it was Christmas,

1:19:15.000 --> 1:19:17.878
but because you love her and me.

1:19:19.087 --> 1:19:22.799
And when we needed you most,
you were there all in.

1:19:23.425 --> 1:19:26.219
And that's the kind of magic
that I want to believe in.

1:19:27.345 --> 1:19:28.597
Aw.

1:19:29.181 --> 1:19:30.348
Amen, sister.

1:19:31.641 --> 1:19:34.394
And that thing
that I said the other night,

1:19:34.978 --> 1:19:36.104
could I take that back?

1:19:36.188 --> 1:19:37.731
Please. Yes. Please.

1:19:37.814 --> 1:19:40.066
-I agree, yes, thank you.
-Mmm.

1:19:40.984 --> 1:19:41.818
Called it.

1:19:41.902 --> 1:19:43.904
Yeah, it didn't take a genius.

1:19:44.654 --> 1:19:47.407
-But I have one more thing,
-Oh, but I had one more thing.

1:19:47.491 --> 1:19:50.076
-Well, is your thing my thing?
-I don't know what your thing is.

1:19:50.160 --> 1:19:52.370
-Maybe you just do your thing.
-You should do your thing.

1:19:52.454 --> 1:19:54.164
Someone do their thing.

1:19:55.791 --> 1:19:57.459
You do it. You do it, please.

1:19:57.542 --> 1:19:58.502
Okay.

1:19:59.878 --> 1:20:04.883
Tom, I don't ever want you
to lose your belief in Santa,

1:20:05.425 --> 1:20:06.635
your love of Christmas.

1:20:07.427 --> 1:20:09.221
Because you've taught me
how important it is

1:20:09.304 --> 1:20:12.015
to believe in something
bigger than ourselves.

1:20:12.891 --> 1:20:14.392
And something we can't prove.

1:20:15.018 --> 1:20:16.520
And that every grown-up

1:20:16.603 --> 1:20:19.898
should be able to tap into
that childlike wonder

1:20:19.981 --> 1:20:21.983
that just makes life sweeter.

1:20:22.526 --> 1:20:23.735
Oh.

1:20:24.820 --> 1:20:26.196
Wait, they're not done yet.

1:20:26.738 --> 1:20:29.741
Stay right there. Just gonna do my thing.

1:20:30.325 --> 1:20:32.160
-It's a different thing.
-I knew it.

1:20:33.620 --> 1:20:35.497
I made this list.

1:20:36.331 --> 1:20:40.168
This is my wish list for Santa this year.

1:20:48.260 --> 1:20:49.094
That's it.

1:20:50.178 --> 1:20:51.847
This is everything I want.

1:20:53.390 --> 1:20:54.224
It's us.

1:20:57.686 --> 1:21:02.607
Ella, you are the coolest kid
I have ever met,

1:21:03.191 --> 1:21:07.028
and I promise to always be your friend.

1:21:12.075 --> 1:21:12.951
And Lisa.

1:21:15.078 --> 1:21:20.208
I love you more than
I could even put into words.

1:21:21.209 --> 1:21:22.043
So…

1:21:23.587 --> 1:21:27.048
Instead, I am going
to take a leap of faith

1:21:27.841 --> 1:21:29.634
that our love

1:21:30.218 --> 1:21:36.224
and our future together
will be even bigger than Santa Claus.

1:21:47.527 --> 1:21:49.195
Shut the front door.

1:21:51.197 --> 1:21:52.115
Oh.

1:21:57.704 --> 1:21:59.247
Lisa Ann Russell…

1:22:02.042 --> 1:22:03.293
will you marry me?

1:22:08.798 --> 1:22:11.885
I never expected my proposal
to include Santa Claus.

1:22:13.094 --> 1:22:16.348
-Yes! Yes.
-Yes? Oh good.

1:22:17.557 --> 1:22:18.975
Yes! Whoo!

1:22:19.059 --> 1:22:19.893
Yes!

1:22:22.938 --> 1:22:24.564
He is real.

1:22:24.648 --> 1:22:25.482
What?

1:22:25.565 --> 1:22:27.025
Santa is real.

1:22:28.568 --> 1:22:30.487
That's what I asked him for.

1:22:30.987 --> 1:22:32.781
That you and Tom would get married.

1:22:32.864 --> 1:22:34.199
And now you're gonna.

1:22:43.625 --> 1:22:45.335
You can't argue with logic like that.

1:22:50.590 --> 1:22:52.926
Come here. Come here.

1:22:53.009 --> 1:22:55.095
Give me some of that. Aw.

1:22:55.178 --> 1:22:56.596
Oh!

1:22:58.139 --> 1:22:58.974
Boom!

1:22:59.057 --> 1:23:01.267
I did it! I am a man!

1:23:02.477 --> 1:23:05.063
-Ooh! Oh my God, I am sweating.
-You feeling good? Yeah.

1:23:05.146 --> 1:23:06.564
-Every part of me.
-Yeah.

1:23:09.150 --> 1:23:10.068
<i>Christmas.</i>

1:23:10.735 --> 1:23:11.861
<i>Love it or dread it,</i>

1:23:11.945 --> 1:23:15.657
<i>it's the one time of year</i>
<i>when everyone's on the same page.</i>

1:23:16.533 --> 1:23:20.328
<i>Want to turn your house</i>
<i>into a temporary Mardi Gras celebration?</i>

1:23:21.121 --> 1:23:24.374
<i>No need to worry</i>
<i>about your neighbors getting mad.</i>

1:23:24.457 --> 1:23:27.419
<i>They'll turn out in droves</i>
<i>to admire it instead.</i>

1:23:31.172 --> 1:23:33.133
<i>Haven't seen your relatives in a while?</i>

1:23:33.216 --> 1:23:34.050
Ah!

1:23:34.843 --> 1:23:37.887
<i>Take those travel delays</i>
<i>in stride, friends,</i>

1:23:37.971 --> 1:23:41.516
<i>because you're not the only ones</i>
<i>making a journey to reconnect.</i>

1:23:43.893 --> 1:23:48.273
<i>For a short time, the pressures</i>
<i>and the deadlines of our fast-paced world</i>

1:23:48.356 --> 1:23:52.318
<i>give way to traditions both old and new.</i>

1:24:06.041 --> 1:24:07.751
<i>It's Santa's Christmas.</i>

1:24:08.376 --> 1:24:11.129
<i>He transcends country and religion.</i>

1:24:11.629 --> 1:24:14.549
<i>He is unrivaled.</i>
<i>You either believe in him…</i>

1:24:16.009 --> 1:24:16.968
<i>or you don't.</i>

1:24:19.846 --> 1:24:24.059
<i>And we should never doubt the power</i>
<i>of taking our little leaps of faith.</i>

1:24:24.893 --> 1:24:30.940
<i>Faith may be the last great universal</i>
<i>concept holding the whole world together.</i>

1:24:37.322 --> 1:24:41.076
"And besides,
a little magic never hurt anybody."

1:24:42.118 --> 1:24:44.329
"Merry Christmas everyone."

1:24:44.412 --> 1:24:45.830
Aw.

1:24:45.914 --> 1:24:48.416
-Do you like it?
-I love it.

1:24:49.000 --> 1:24:50.001
Mwah.

